erly for adoption as sons, the redemption of our bodies.'),(27,2,'Luke 1:68','“Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, for he has visited and redeemed his people'),(28,2,'1 Timothy 2:6','who gave himself as a ransom for all, which is the testimony given at the proper time.'),(29,2,'2 Corinthians 1:10','He delivered us from such a deadly peril, and he will deliver us. On him we have set our hope that he will deliver us again.'),(30,2,'Romans 3:24','and are justified by his grace as a gift, through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus.'),(31,2,'1 Corinthians 1:30','And because of him you are in Christ Jesus, who became to us wisdom from God, righteousness and sanctification and redemption.'),(32,2,'Psalm 130:7','O Israel, hope in the Lord! For with the Lord there is steadfast love, and with him is plentiful redemption.'),(33,2,'Isaiah 44:22','I have blotted out your transgressions like a cloud and your sins like mist; return to me, for I have redeemed you.'),(34,3,'Joshua 1:9','Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be frightened, and do not be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.'),(35,3,'2 Timothy 1:7','For God gave us a spirit not of fear but of power and love and self-control.'),(36,3,'Isaiah 41:10','Fear not, for I am with you; be not dismayed, for I am your God; I will strengthen you, I will help you, I will uphold you with my righteous right hand.'),(37,3,'Psalm 27:1','The Lord is my light and my salvation; whom shall I fear? The Lord is the stronghold of my life; of whom shall I be afraid?'),(38,3,'1 Corinthians 16:13','Be watchful, stand firm in the faith, act like men, be strong.'),(39,3,'Psalm 31:24','Be strong, and let your heart take courage, all you who wait for the Lord!'),(40,3,'Deuteronomy 31:6','Be strong and courageous. Do not fear or be in dread of them, for it is the Lord your God who goes with you. He will not leave you or forsake you.'),(41,3,'Hebrews 13:6','So we can confidently say, “The Lord is my helper; I will not fear; what can man do to me?”'),(42,3,'Matthew 14:27','But immediately Jesus spoke to them, saying, “Take heart; it is I. Do not be afraid.”'),(43,3,'Psalm 118:6','The Lord is on my side; I will not fear. What can man do to me?'),(44,3,'Ephesians 6:10','Finally, be strong in the Lord and in the strength of his might.'),(45,3,'Romans 8:31','What then shall we say to these things? If God is for us, who can be against us?'),(46,3,'Philippians 4:13','I can do all things through him who strengthens me.'),(47,3,'2 Chronicles 32:7','“Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid or dismayed before the king of Assyria and all the horde that is with him, for there are more with us than with him.'),(48,3,'John 16:33','I have said these things to you, that in me you may have peace. In the world you will have tribulation. But take heart; I have overcome the world.'),(49,4,'Proverbs 3:5-6','Trust in the Lord with all your heart, and do not lean on your own understanding. In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make straight your paths.'),(50,4,'James 1:5','If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives generously to all without reproach, and it will be given him.'),(51,4,'Proverbs 2:6','For the Lord gives wisdom; from his mouth come knowledge and understanding.'),(52,4,'Proverbs 4:7','The beginning of wisdom is this: Get wisdom, and whatever you get, get insight.'),(53,4,'Ecclesiastes 7:12','For wisdom is a defense as money is a defense, but the excellency of knowledge is, that wisdom gives life to them that have it.'),(54,4,'Proverbs 9:10','The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom, and the knowledge of the Holy One is insight.'),(55,4,'Colossians 2:3','In whom are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.'),(56,4,'Job 28:28','And he said to man, “Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom; and to turn away from evil is understanding.”'),(57,4,'Psalm 111:10','The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom; all those who practice it 